cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 75 mi WNW of Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic
cyclone.trajectory: moving west-northwest across Hispaniola, forecast to pass near the Turks & Caicos and SE Bahamas, skirt or cross the N coast of Cuba, then curve into the eastern Gulf of Mexico and approach the northern Gulf Coast early next week

weather_observation.watch_coast: Haiti from the northern border to Gonaives; Turks & Caicos Islands; southeastern Bahamas; Cuban provinces of Ciego de Avila, Camaguey, Las Tunas, Holguin, Granma, Santiago de Cuba, and Guantanamo
weather_observation.warning_coast: Dominican Republic south coast from Punta Palenque eastward and north coast from the Dominican Republic/Haiti border eastward
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Hispaniola, Turks & Caicos, Bahamas, northern coast of Cuba, Florida Keys and Peninsula, and the northern Gulf Coast
